                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17881022-9-off37 t17881022-9-crimeloc41"></join>;<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178810220008"></xptr>he had lived with me some months; the stockings were found by my shopman, in a hat-box, concealed in the prisoner's bed; I saw them taken out; the bed is in the counter in the shop, where the prisoner used to sleep; my shopman had lost half a guinea, and he suspected the prisoner, having seen him doing something about the bed, which induced him to search, and he there found the stockings; I spoke to the boy, and asked him what he put the stockings there for; he said, he wanted to shew them to his mother, to buy him some of the same sort, as the shopman had refused to sell him any.</p>
